text:
Good-bye unto the life I once did live,
And to the world I once did know;
And kiss the hills for me, but once alone;
Now am I ready to go!

source_text:
Good-by to the life I used to live,
And the world I used to know;
And kiss the hills for me, just once;
Now I am ready to go!

text:
’Twad be owre lang a tale to tell,
How mony a story’s past;
And how they throng’d unto the yill,
When they were a’ dismiss’d;
How drink went round, in cogs and caups,
Amang the furms and benches;
And cheese and bread, frae women’s laps,
Were dealt in lunches
And dawds that day.

source_text:
’Twad be owre lang a tale to tell,
How mony stories past;
An’ how they crouded to the yill,
When they were a’ dismist;
How drink gaed round, in cogs an’ caups,
Amang the furms an’ benches;
An’ cheese an’ bread, frae women’s laps,
Was dealt about in lunches
An’ dawds that day.

text:
The hands still clasp the laggard glass;
The lips I would have chilled, alas!
Are cold too needless, too unrolled,

