text:
Come, bring to me a pint o’ wine,
And pour it in a silver tassie;
That I may drink ere I depart,
A token to my bonie lassie.
The boat she reels at Leith’s own pier;
Fu’ loud the wind blaws frae the Ferry;
The ship glides by the Berwick-law,
And I maun part wi’ my bonie Mary.

source_text:
Go, fetch to me a pint o’ wine,
And fill it in a silver tassie;
That I may drink before I go,
A service to my bonie lassie.
The boat rocks at the pier o’ Leith;
Fu’ loud the wind blaws frae the Ferry;
The ship rides by the Berwick-law,
And I maun leave my bonie Mary.
